l of the latter. In the United States, this is mainly used as a girl's name, perhaps under the influence of   Audrey ."],"variants":[{"name":"Aubree","meanings":["From a Norman French form of the Germanic name <i>Alberic</i>, from <i>alb</i> ‘elf, supernatural being’ + <i>ric</i> ‘power’. This was the name, according to Germanic mythology, of the king of the elves. The native Old English form, <i>Ælfrīc</i>, borne by a 10th-century archbishop of Canterbury, did not long survive the Conquest. <i>Aubrey</i> was a relatively common given name during the Middle Ages, but later fell out of favour. Its occurrence since the 19th century may in part represent a transferred use of the surname derived from the Norman given name, as well as a revival of the latter. In the United States, this is mainly used as a girl's name, perhaps under the influence of   Audrey ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Aubrey Conteville was born in 1263, in Stringston, Somerset, England, United Kingdom. She married Hugh Fichett in 1298, in England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in Somerset, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1263–":"1263–Surnud","1250–1314":"1250–1314","1300–1400":"1300–1400","1263–Female":"1263–Surnud","1314":"1314","1400":"1400","1300":"1300","1298":"1298","1263":"1263","1250":"1250","Somerset, England":"Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Stringston, Somerset, England":"Stringston, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Enmore, Somerset, England":"Enmore, Somerset, England"},"fi":{"1263–":"1263–Kuollut","1250–1314":"1250–1314","1300–1400":"1300–1400","1263–Female":"1263–Kuollut","1314":"1314","1400":"1400","1300":"1300","1298":"1298","1263":"1263","1250":"1250","Somerset, England":"Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Stringston, Somerset, England":"Stringston, Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Enmore, Somerset, England":"Enmore, Somerset, England"}